cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.SC 

The paper deals with the combination of polyhedral analysis and predicate partitioning to compute inductive invariants for programs with disjunctions and existential quantifiers. This falls under the area of program verification and formal methods, which is typically categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of linear programming and satisfiability modulo theory (SMT) solving, which are also relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). The paper also discusses implementation and performance issues, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
